The paper focuses on the problem of autonomous sorting in industrial robotics, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed solution involves using deep CNN feature extraction and clustering algorithms, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) research. The paper also mentions instance retrieval and supervised classification, which are topics in information retrieval (cs.IR). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO, followed by cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.IR.
